86 void Player::SetVirtualItemSlot(uint8 i, Item* item)
87 {
88  ASSERT(i < 3);
89  if (i < 2 && item)
90  {
91  if (!item->GetEnchantmentId(TEMP_ENCHANTMENT_SLOT))
92  return;
93  uint32 charges = item->GetEnchantmentCharges(TEMP_ENCHANTMENT_SLOT);
94  if (charges == 0)
95  return;
96  if (charges > 1)
97  item->SetEnchantmentCharges(TEMP_ENCHANTMENT_SLOT, charges - 1);
98  else if (charges <= 1)
99  {
100  ApplyEnchantment(item, TEMP_ENCHANTMENT_SLOT, false);
101  item->ClearEnchantment(TEMP_ENCHANTMENT_SLOT);
102  }
103  }
104 }
105 
106 void Player::SetSheath(SheathState sheathed)
107 {
108  switch (sheathed)
109  {
110  case SHEATH_STATE_UNARMED: // no prepared weapon
111  SetVirtualItemSlot(0, nullptr);
112  SetVirtualItemSlot(1, nullptr);
113  SetVirtualItemSlot(2, nullptr);
114  break;
115  case SHEATH_STATE_MELEE: // prepared melee weapon
116  SetVirtualItemSlot(0, GetWeaponForAttack(BASE_ATTACK, true));
117  SetVirtualItemSlot(1, GetWeaponForAttack(OFF_ATTACK, true));
118  SetVirtualItemSlot(2, nullptr);
119  break;
120  case SHEATH_STATE_RANGED: // prepared ranged weapon
121  SetVirtualItemSlot(0, nullptr);
122  SetVirtualItemSlot(1, nullptr);
123  SetVirtualItemSlot(2, GetWeaponForAttack(RANGED_ATTACK, true));
124  break;
125  default:
126  SetVirtualItemSlot(0, nullptr);
127  SetVirtualItemSlot(1, nullptr);
128  SetVirtualItemSlot(2, nullptr);
129  break;
130  }
131  Unit::SetSheath(sheathed); // this must visualize Sheath changing for other players...
132 }

134 uint8 Player::FindEquipSlot(ItemTemplate const* proto, uint32 slot, bool swap) const
135 {
136  uint8 playerClass = getClass();
137 
138  uint8 slots[4];
139  slots[0] = NULL_SLOT;
140  slots[1] = NULL_SLOT;
141  slots[2] = NULL_SLOT;
142  slots[3] = NULL_SLOT;
143  switch (proto->InventoryType)
144  {
145  case INVTYPE_HEAD:
146  slots[0] = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_HEAD;
147  break;
148  case INVTYPE_NECK:
149  slots[0] = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_NECK;
150  break;
151  case INVTYPE_SHOULDERS:
152  slots[0] = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_SHOULDERS;
153  break;
154  case INVTYPE_BODY:
155  slots[0] = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_BODY;
156  break;
157  case INVTYPE_CHEST:
158  case INVTYPE_ROBE:
159  slots[0] = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_CHEST;
160  break;
161  case INVTYPE_WAIST:
162  slots[0] = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_WAIST;
163  break;
164  case INVTYPE_LEGS:
165  slots[0] = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_LEGS;
166  break;
167  case INVTYPE_FEET:
168  slots[0] = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_FEET;
169  break;
170  case INVTYPE_WRISTS:
171  slots[0] = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_WRISTS;
172  break;
173  case INVTYPE_HANDS:
174  slots[0] = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_HANDS;
175  break;
176  case INVTYPE_FINGER:
177  slots[0] = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_FINGER1;
178  slots[1] = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_FINGER2;
179  break;
180  case INVTYPE_TRINKET:
181  slots[0] = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_TRINKET1;
182  slots[1] = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_TRINKET2;
183  break;
184  case INVTYPE_CLOAK:
185  slots[0] = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_BACK;
186  break;
187  case INVTYPE_WEAPON:
188  {
189  slots[0] = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_MAINHAND;
190 
191  // suggest offhand slot only if know dual wielding
192  // (this will be replace mainhand weapon at auto equip instead unwonted "you don't known dual wielding" ...
193  if (CanDualWield())
194  slots[1] = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_OFFHAND;
195  break;
196  }
197  case INVTYPE_SHIELD:
198  case INVTYPE_WEAPONOFFHAND:
199  case INVTYPE_HOLDABLE:
200  slots[0] = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_OFFHAND;
201  break;
202  case INVTYPE_RANGED:
203  case INVTYPE_RANGEDRIGHT:
204  case INVTYPE_THROWN:
205  slots[0] = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_RANGED;
206  break;
207  case INVTYPE_2HWEAPON:
208  slots[0] = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_MAINHAND;
209  if (Item* mhWeapon = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, EQUIPMENT_SLOT_MAINHAND))
210  {
211  if (ItemTemplate const* mhWeaponProto = mhWeapon->GetTemplate())
212  {
213  if (mhWeaponProto->SubClass == ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_POLEARM || mhWeaponProto->SubClass == ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_STAFF)
214  {
215  const_cast<Player*>(this)->AutoUnequipOffhandIfNeed(true);
216  break;
217  }
218  }
219  }
220 
221  if (GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, EQUIPMENT_SLOT_OFFHAND))
222  {
223  if (proto->SubClass == ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_POLEARM || proto->SubClass == ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_STAFF)
224  {
225  const_cast<Player*>(this)->AutoUnequipOffhandIfNeed(true);
226  break;
227  }
228  }
229  if (CanDualWield() && CanTitanGrip() && proto->SubClass != ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_POLEARM && proto->SubClass != ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_STAFF && proto->SubClass != ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_FISHING_POLE)
230  slots[1] = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_OFFHAND;
231  break;
232  case INVTYPE_TABARD:
233  slots[0] = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_TABARD;
234  break;
235  case INVTYPE_WEAPONMAINHAND:
236  slots[0] = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_MAINHAND;
237  break;
238  case INVTYPE_BAG:
239  slots[0] = INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START + 0;
240  slots[1] = INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START + 1;
241  slots[2] = INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START + 2;
242  slots[3] = INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START + 3;
243  break;
244  case INVTYPE_RELIC:
245  {
246  switch (proto->SubClass)
247  {
248  case ITEM_SUBCLASS_ARMOR_LIBRAM:
249  if (playerClass == CLASS_PALADIN)
250  slots[0] = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_RANGED;
251  break;
252  case ITEM_SUBCLASS_ARMOR_IDOL:
253  if (playerClass == CLASS_DRUID)
254  slots[0] = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_RANGED;
255  break;
256  case ITEM_SUBCLASS_ARMOR_TOTEM:
257  if (playerClass == CLASS_SHAMAN)
258  slots[0] = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_RANGED;
259  break;
260  case ITEM_SUBCLASS_ARMOR_MISC:
261  if (playerClass == CLASS_WARLOCK)
262  slots[0] = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_RANGED;
263  break;
264  case ITEM_SUBCLASS_ARMOR_SIGIL:
265  if (playerClass == CLASS_DEATH_KNIGHT)
266  slots[0] = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_RANGED;
267  break;
268  }
269  break;
270  }
271  default:
272  return NULL_SLOT;
273  }
274 
275  if (slot != NULL_SLOT)
276  {
277  if (swap || !GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, slot))
278  for (uint8 i = 0; i < 4; ++i)
279  if (slots[i] == slot)
280  return slot;
281  }
282  else
283  {
284  // search free slot at first
285  for (uint8 i = 0; i < 4; ++i)
286  if (slots[i] != NULL_SLOT && !GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, slots[i]))
287  // in case 2hand equipped weapon (without titan grip) offhand slot empty but not free
288  if (slots[i] != EQUIPMENT_SLOT_OFFHAND || !IsTwoHandUsed())
289  return slots[i];
290 
291  // if not found free and can swap return first appropriate from used
292  for (uint8 i = 0; i < 4; ++i)
293  if (slots[i] != NULL_SLOT && swap)
294  return slots[i];
295  }
296 
297  // no free position
298  return NULL_SLOT;
299 }
300 
301 InventoryResult Player::CanUnequipItems(uint32 item, uint32 count) const
302 {
303  uint32 tempcount = 0;
304 
305  InventoryResult res = EQUIP_ERR_OK;
306 
307  for (uint8 i = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_START; i < INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END; ++i)
308  if (Item* pItem = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i))
309  if (pItem->GetEntry() == item)
310  {
311  InventoryResult ires = CanUnequipItem(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0 << 8 | i, false);
312  if (ires == EQUIP_ERR_OK)
313  {
314  tempcount += pItem->GetCount();
315  if (tempcount >= count)
316  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
317  }
318  else
319  res = ires;
320  }
321 
322  for (uint8 i = INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_START; i < INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_END; ++i)
323  if (Item* pItem = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i))
324  if (pItem->GetEntry() == item)
325  {
326  tempcount += pItem->GetCount();
327  if (tempcount >= count)
328  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
329  }
330 
331  for (uint8 i = KEYRING_SLOT_START; i < CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_END; ++i)
332  if (Item* pItem = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i))
333  if (pItem->GetEntry() == item)
334  {
335  tempcount += pItem->GetCount();
336  if (tempcount >= count)
337  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
338  }
339 
340  for (uint8 i = INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START; i < INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END; ++i)
341  if (Bag* pBag = GetBagByPos(i))
342  for (uint32 j = 0; j < pBag->GetBagSize(); ++j)
343  if (Item* pItem = GetItemByPos(i, j))
344  if (pItem->GetEntry() == item)
345  {
346  tempcount += pItem->GetCount();
347  if (tempcount >= count)
348  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
349  }
350 
351  // not found req. item count and have unequippable items
352  return res;
353 }
354 
355 uint32 Player::GetItemCount(uint32 item, bool inBankAlso, Item* skipItem) const
356 {
357  uint32 count = 0;
358  for (uint8 i = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_START; i < INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_END; i++)
359  if (Item* pItem = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i))
360  if (pItem != skipItem && pItem->GetEntry() == item)
361  count += pItem->GetCount();
362 
363  for (uint8 i = KEYRING_SLOT_START; i < CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_END; ++i)
364  if (Item* pItem = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i))
365  if (pItem != skipItem && pItem->GetEntry() == item)
366  count += pItem->GetCount();
367 
368  for (uint8 i = INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START; i < INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END; ++i)
369  if (Bag* pBag = GetBagByPos(i))
370  count += pBag->GetItemCount(item, skipItem);
371 
372  if (skipItem && skipItem->GetTemplate()->GemProperties)
373  for (uint8 i = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_START; i < INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_END; ++i)
374  if (Item* pItem = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i))
375  if (pItem != skipItem && pItem->GetTemplate()->Socket[0].Color)
376  count += pItem->GetGemCountWithID(item);
377 
378  if (inBankAlso)
379  {
380  // checking every item from 39 to 74 (including bank bags)
381  for (uint8 i = BANK_SLOT_ITEM_START; i < BANK_SLOT_BAG_END; ++i)
382  if (Item* pItem = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i))
383  if (pItem != skipItem && pItem->GetEntry() == item)
384  count += pItem->GetCount();
385 
386  for (uint8 i = BANK_SLOT_BAG_START; i < BANK_SLOT_BAG_END; ++i)
387  if (Bag* pBag = GetBagByPos(i))
388  count += pBag->GetItemCount(item, skipItem);
389 
390  if (skipItem && skipItem->GetTemplate()->GemProperties)
391  for (uint8 i = BANK_SLOT_ITEM_START; i < BANK_SLOT_ITEM_END; ++i)
392  if (Item* pItem = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i))
393  if (pItem != skipItem && pItem->GetTemplate()->Socket[0].Color)
394  count += pItem->GetGemCountWithID(item);
395  }
396 
397  return count;
398 }
399 
400 uint32 Player::GetItemCountWithLimitCategory(uint32 limitCategory, Item* skipItem) const
401 {
402  uint32 count = 0;
403  for (int i = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_START; i < INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_END; ++i)
404  if (Item* pItem = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i))
405  if (pItem != skipItem)
406  if (ItemTemplate const* pProto = pItem->GetTemplate())
407  if (pProto->ItemLimitCategory == limitCategory)
408  count += pItem->GetCount();
409 
410  for (int i = KEYRING_SLOT_START; i < CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_END; ++i)
411  if (Item* pItem = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i))
412  if (pItem != skipItem)
413  if (ItemTemplate const* pProto = pItem->GetTemplate())
414  if (pProto->ItemLimitCategory == limitCategory)
415  count += pItem->GetCount();
416 
417  for (int i = INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START; i < INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END; ++i)
418  if (Bag* pBag = GetBagByPos(i))
419  count += pBag->GetItemCountWithLimitCategory(limitCategory, skipItem);
420 
421  for (int i = BANK_SLOT_ITEM_START; i < BANK_SLOT_BAG_END; ++i)
422  if (Item* pItem = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i))
423  if (pItem != skipItem)
424  if (ItemTemplate const* pProto = pItem->GetTemplate())
425  if (pProto->ItemLimitCategory == limitCategory)
426  count += pItem->GetCount();
427 
428  for (int i = BANK_SLOT_BAG_START; i < BANK_SLOT_BAG_END; ++i)
429  if (Bag* pBag = GetBagByPos(i))
430  count += pBag->GetItemCountWithLimitCategory(limitCategory, skipItem);
431 
432  return count;
433 }

435 Item* Player::GetItemByGuid(ObjectGuid guid) const
436 {
437  for (uint8 i = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_START; i < INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_END; ++i)
438  if (Item* pItem = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i))
439  if (pItem->GetGUID() == guid)
440  return pItem;
441 
442  for (uint8 i = KEYRING_SLOT_START; i < CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_END; ++i)
443  if (Item* pItem = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i))
444  if (pItem->GetGUID() == guid)
445  return pItem;
446 
447  for (int i = BANK_SLOT_ITEM_START; i < BANK_SLOT_BAG_END; ++i)
448  if (Item* pItem = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i))
449  if (pItem->GetGUID() == guid)
450  return pItem;
451 
452  for (uint8 i = INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START; i < INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END; ++i)
453  if (Bag* pBag = GetBagByPos(i))
454  for (uint32 j = 0; j < pBag->GetBagSize(); ++j)
455  if (Item* pItem = pBag->GetItemByPos(j))
456  if (pItem->GetGUID() == guid)
457  return pItem;
458 
459  for (uint8 i = BANK_SLOT_BAG_START; i < BANK_SLOT_BAG_END; ++i)
460  if (Bag* pBag = GetBagByPos(i))
461  for (uint32 j = 0; j < pBag->GetBagSize(); ++j)
462  if (Item* pItem = pBag->GetItemByPos(j))
463  if (pItem->GetGUID() == guid)
464  return pItem;
465 
466  return nullptr;
467 }

469 Item* Player::GetItemByPos(uint16 pos) const
470 {
471  uint8 bag = pos >> 8;
472  uint8 slot = pos & 255;
473  return GetItemByPos(bag, slot);
474 }
475 
476 Item* Player::GetItemByPos(uint8 bag, uint8 slot) const
477 {
478  if (bag == INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0 && (slot < BANK_SLOT_BAG_END || (slot >= KEYRING_SLOT_START && slot < CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_END)))
479  return m_items[slot];
480  else if (Bag* pBag = GetBagByPos(bag))
481  return pBag->GetItemByPos(slot);
482  return nullptr;
483 }
484 
485 Bag* Player::GetBagByPos(uint8 bag) const
486 {
487  if ((bag >= INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START && bag < INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END)
488  || (bag >= BANK_SLOT_BAG_START && bag < BANK_SLOT_BAG_END))
489  if (Item* item = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, bag))
490  return item->ToBag();
491  return nullptr;
492 }
493 
494 uint32 Player::GetFreeInventorySpace() const
495 {
496  uint32 freeSpace = 0;
497 
498  // Check backpack
499  for (uint8 slot = INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_START; slot < INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_END; ++slot)
500  {
501  Item* item = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, slot);
502  if (!item)
503  freeSpace += 1;
504  }
505 
506  // Check bags
507  for (uint8 i = INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START; i < INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END; i++)
508  {
509  if (Bag* bag = GetBagByPos(i))
510  freeSpace += bag->GetFreeSlots();
511  }
512 
513  return freeSpace;
514 }
515 
516 Item* Player::GetWeaponForAttack(WeaponAttackType attackType, bool useable /*= false*/) const
517 {
518  uint8 slot;
519  switch (attackType)
520  {
521  case BASE_ATTACK:
522  slot = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_MAINHAND;
523  break;
524  case OFF_ATTACK:
525  slot = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_OFFHAND;
526  break;
527  case RANGED_ATTACK:
528  slot = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_RANGED;
529  break;
530  default:
531  return nullptr;
532  }
533 
534  Item* item = nullptr;
535  if (useable)
536  item = GetUseableItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, slot);
537  else
538  item = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, slot);
539  if (!item || item->GetTemplate()->Class != ITEM_CLASS_WEAPON)
540  return nullptr;
541 
542  if (!useable)
543  return item;
544 
545  if (item->IsBroken() || IsInFeralForm())
546  return nullptr;
547 
548  return item;
549 }
550 
551 Item* Player::GetShield(bool useable) const
552 {
553  Item* item = nullptr;
554  if (useable)
555  item = GetUseableItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, EQUIPMENT_SLOT_OFFHAND);
556  else
557  item = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, EQUIPMENT_SLOT_OFFHAND);
558  if (!item || item->GetTemplate()->Class != ITEM_CLASS_ARMOR)
559  return nullptr;
560 
561  if (!useable)
562  return item;
563 
564  if (item->IsBroken())
565  return nullptr;
566 
567  return item;
568 }

570 uint8 Player::GetAttackBySlot(uint8 slot)
571 {
572  switch (slot)
573  {
574  case EQUIPMENT_SLOT_MAINHAND:
575  return BASE_ATTACK;
576  case EQUIPMENT_SLOT_OFFHAND:
577  return OFF_ATTACK;
578  case EQUIPMENT_SLOT_RANGED:
579  return RANGED_ATTACK;
580  default:
581  return MAX_ATTACK;
582  }
583 }
584 
585 bool Player::IsInventoryPos(uint8 bag, uint8 slot)
586 {
587  if (bag == INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0 && slot == NULL_SLOT)
588  return true;
589  if (bag == INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0 && (slot >= INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_START && slot < INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_END))
590  return true;
591  if (bag >= INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START && bag < INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END)
592  return true;
593  if (bag == INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0 && (slot >= KEYRING_SLOT_START && slot < CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_END))
594  return true;
595  return false;
596 }
597 
598 bool Player::IsEquipmentPos(uint8 bag, uint8 slot)
599 {
600  if (bag == INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0 && (slot < EQUIPMENT_SLOT_END))
601  return true;
602  if (bag == INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0 && (slot >= INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START && slot < INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END))
603  return true;
604  return false;
605 }

607 bool Player::IsBankPos(uint8 bag, uint8 slot)
608 {
609  if (bag == INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0 && (slot >= BANK_SLOT_ITEM_START && slot < BANK_SLOT_ITEM_END))
610  return true;
611  if (bag == INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0 && (slot >= BANK_SLOT_BAG_START && slot < BANK_SLOT_BAG_END))
612  return true;
613  if (bag >= BANK_SLOT_BAG_START && bag < BANK_SLOT_BAG_END)
614  return true;
615  return false;
616 }
617 
618 bool Player::IsBagPos(uint16 pos)
619 {
620  uint8 bag = pos >> 8;
621  uint8 slot = pos & 255;
622  if (bag == INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0 && (slot >= INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START && slot < INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END))
623  return true;
624  if (bag == INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0 && (slot >= BANK_SLOT_BAG_START && slot < BANK_SLOT_BAG_END))
625  return true;
626  return false;
627 }
628 
629 bool Player::IsValidPos(uint8 bag, uint8 slot, bool explicit_pos)
630 {
631  // post selected
632  if (bag == NULL_BAG && !explicit_pos)
633  return true;
634 
635  if (bag == INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0)
636  {
637  // any post selected
638  if (slot == NULL_SLOT && !explicit_pos)
639  return true;
640 
641  // equipment
642  if (slot < EQUIPMENT_SLOT_END)
643  return true;
644 
645  // bag equip slots
646  if (slot >= INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START && slot < INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END)
647  return true;
648 
649  // backpack slots
650  if (slot >= INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_START && slot < INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_END)
651  return true;
652 
653  // keyring slots
654  if (slot >= KEYRING_SLOT_START && slot < KEYRING_SLOT_END)
655  return true;
656 
657  // bank main slots
658  if (slot >= BANK_SLOT_ITEM_START && slot < BANK_SLOT_ITEM_END)
659  return true;
660 
661  // bank bag slots
662  if (slot >= BANK_SLOT_BAG_START && slot < BANK_SLOT_BAG_END)
663  return true;
664 
665  return false;
666  }
667 
668  // bag content slots
669  // bank bag content slots
670  if (Bag* pBag = GetBagByPos(bag))
671  {
672  // any post selected
673  if (slot == NULL_SLOT && !explicit_pos)
674  return true;
675 
676  return slot < pBag->GetBagSize();
677  }
678 
679  // where this?
680  return false;
681 }

683 bool Player::HasItemCount(uint32 item, uint32 count, bool inBankAlso) const
684 {
685  uint32 tempcount = 0;
686  for (uint8 i = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_START; i < INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_END; i++)
687  {
688  Item* pItem = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i);
689  if (pItem && pItem->GetEntry() == item && !pItem->IsInTrade())
690  {
691  tempcount += pItem->GetCount();
692  if (tempcount >= count)
693  return true;
694  }
695  }
696  for (uint8 i = KEYRING_SLOT_START; i < CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_END; ++i)
697  {
698  Item* pItem = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i);
699  if (pItem && pItem->GetEntry() == item && !pItem->IsInTrade())
700  {
701  tempcount += pItem->GetCount();
702  if (tempcount >= count)
703  return true;
704  }
705  }
706  for (uint8 i = INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START; i < INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END; i++)
707  {
708  if (Bag* pBag = GetBagByPos(i))
709  {
710  for (uint32 j = 0; j < pBag->GetBagSize(); j++)
711  {
712  Item* pItem = GetItemByPos(i, j);
713  if (pItem && pItem->GetEntry() == item && !pItem->IsInTrade())
714  {
715  tempcount += pItem->GetCount();
716  if (tempcount >= count)
717  return true;
718  }
719  }
720  }
721  }
722 
723  if (inBankAlso)
724  {
725  for (uint8 i = BANK_SLOT_ITEM_START; i < BANK_SLOT_ITEM_END; i++)
726  {
727  Item* pItem = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i);
728  if (pItem && pItem->GetEntry() == item && !pItem->IsInTrade())
729  {
730  tempcount += pItem->GetCount();
731  if (tempcount >= count)
732  return true;
733  }
734  }
735  for (uint8 i = BANK_SLOT_BAG_START; i < BANK_SLOT_BAG_END; i++)
736  {
737  if (Bag* pBag = GetBagByPos(i))
738  {
739  for (uint32 j = 0; j < pBag->GetBagSize(); j++)
740  {
741  Item* pItem = GetItemByPos(i, j);
742  if (pItem && pItem->GetEntry() == item && !pItem->IsInTrade())
743  {
744  tempcount += pItem->GetCount();
745  if (tempcount >= count)
746  return true;
747  }
748  }
749  }
750  }
751  }
752 
753  return false;
754 }

756 bool Player::HasItemOrGemWithIdEquipped(uint32 item, uint32 count, uint8 except_slot) const
757 {
758  uint32 tempcount = 0;
759  for (uint8 i = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_START; i < EQUIPMENT_SLOT_END; ++i)
760  {
761  if (i == except_slot)
762  continue;
763 
764  Item* pItem = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i);
765  if (pItem && pItem->GetEntry() == item)
766  {
767  tempcount += pItem->GetCount();
768  if (tempcount >= count)
769  return true;
770  }
771  }
772 
773  ItemTemplate const* pProto = sObjectMgr->GetItemTemplate(item);
774  if (pProto && pProto->GemProperties)
775  {
776  for (uint8 i = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_START; i < EQUIPMENT_SLOT_END; ++i)
777  {
778  if (i == except_slot)
779  continue;
780 
781  Item* pItem = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i);
782  if (pItem && pItem->GetTemplate()->Socket[0].Color)
783  {
784  tempcount += pItem->GetGemCountWithID(item);
785  if (tempcount >= count)
786  return true;
787  }
788  }
789  }
790 
791  return false;
792 }
793 
794 bool Player::HasItemOrGemWithLimitCategoryEquipped(uint32 limitCategory, uint32 count, uint8 except_slot) const
795 {
796  uint32 tempcount = 0;
797  for (uint8 i = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_START; i < EQUIPMENT_SLOT_END; ++i)
798  {
799  if (i == except_slot)
800  continue;
801 
802  Item* pItem = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i);
803  if (!pItem)
804  continue;
805 
806  ItemTemplate const* pProto = pItem->GetTemplate();
807  if (!pProto)
808  continue;
809 
810  if (pProto->ItemLimitCategory == limitCategory)
811  {
812  tempcount += pItem->GetCount();
813  if (tempcount >= count)
814  return true;
815  }
816 
817  if (pProto->Socket[0].Color || pItem->GetEnchantmentId(PRISMATIC_ENCHANTMENT_SLOT))
818  {
819  tempcount += pItem->GetGemCountWithLimitCategory(limitCategory);
820  if (tempcount >= count)
821  return true;
822  }
823  }
824 
825  return false;
826 }
827 
828 InventoryResult Player::CanTakeMoreSimilarItems(uint32 entry, uint32 count, Item* pItem, uint32* no_space_count) const
829 {
830  ItemTemplate const* pProto = sObjectMgr->GetItemTemplate(entry);
831  if (!pProto)
832  {
833  if (no_space_count)
834  *no_space_count = count;
835  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_CARRY_MORE_OF_THIS;
836  }
837 
838  // no maximum
839  if ((pProto->MaxCount <= 0 && pProto->ItemLimitCategory == 0) || pProto->MaxCount == 2147483647)
840  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
841 
842  if (pProto->MaxCount > 0)
843  {
844  uint32 curcount = GetItemCount(pProto->ItemId, true, pItem);
845  if (curcount + count > uint32(pProto->MaxCount))
846  {
847  if (no_space_count)
848  *no_space_count = count + curcount - pProto->MaxCount;
849  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_CARRY_MORE_OF_THIS;
850  }
851  }
852 
853  // check unique-equipped limit
854  if (pProto->ItemLimitCategory)
855  {
856  ItemLimitCategoryEntry const* limitEntry = sItemLimitCategoryStore.LookupEntry(pProto->ItemLimitCategory);
857  if (!limitEntry)
858  {
859  if (no_space_count)
860  *no_space_count = count;
861  return EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_CANT_BE_EQUIPPED;
862  }
863 
864  if (limitEntry->mode == ITEM_LIMIT_CATEGORY_MODE_HAVE)
865  {
866  uint32 curcount = GetItemCountWithLimitCategory(pProto->ItemLimitCategory, pItem);
867  if (curcount + count > uint32(limitEntry->maxCount))
868  {
869  if (no_space_count)
870  *no_space_count = count + curcount - limitEntry->maxCount;
871  return EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_MAX_LIMIT_CATEGORY_COUNT_EXCEEDED;
872  }
873  }
874  }
875 
876  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
877 }
878 
879 bool Player::HasItemTotemCategory(uint32 TotemCategory) const
880 {
881  Item* pItem;
882  for (uint8 i = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_START; i < INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_END; ++i)
883  {
884  pItem = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i);
885  if (pItem && IsTotemCategoryCompatiableWith(pItem->GetTemplate(), TotemCategory))
886  return true;
887  }
888  for (uint8 i = KEYRING_SLOT_START; i < CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_END; ++i)
889  {
890  pItem = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i);
891  if (pItem && IsTotemCategoryCompatiableWith(pItem->GetTemplate(), TotemCategory))
892  return true;
893  }
894  for (uint8 i = INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START; i < INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END; ++i)
895  {
896  if (Bag* pBag = GetBagByPos(i))
897  {
898  for (uint32 j = 0; j < pBag->GetBagSize(); ++j)
899  {
900  pItem = GetItemByPos(i, j);
901  if (pItem && IsTotemCategoryCompatiableWith(pItem->GetTemplate(), TotemCategory))
902  return true;
903  }
904  }
905  }
906  return false;
907 }
908 
909 bool Player::IsTotemCategoryCompatiableWith(const ItemTemplate* pProto, uint32 requiredTotemCategoryId) const
910 {
911  if (requiredTotemCategoryId == 0)
912  return true;
913  if (pProto->TotemCategory == 0)
914  return false;
915 
916  TotemCategoryEntry const* itemEntry = sTotemCategoryStore.LookupEntry(pProto->TotemCategory);
917  if (!itemEntry)
918  return false;
919  TotemCategoryEntry const* reqEntry = sTotemCategoryStore.LookupEntry(requiredTotemCategoryId);
920  if (!reqEntry)
921  return false;
922 
923  if (itemEntry->categoryType != reqEntry->categoryType)
924  return false;
925 
926  if ((itemEntry->categoryMask & reqEntry->categoryMask) != reqEntry->categoryMask)
927  return false;
928 
929  // xinef: check skill requirements, needed for enchants!
930  if (pProto->RequiredSkill)
931  if (this->GetSkillValue(pProto->RequiredSkill) < pProto->RequiredSkillRank)
932  return false;
933 
934  return true;
935 }
936 
937 InventoryResult Player::CanStoreItem_InSpecificSlot(uint8 bag, uint8 slot, ItemPosCountVec& dest, ItemTemplate const* pProto, uint32& count, bool swap, Item* pSrcItem) const
938 {
939  Item* pItem2 = GetItemByPos(bag, slot);
940 
941  // ignore move item (this slot will be empty at move)
942  if (pItem2 == pSrcItem)
943  pItem2 = nullptr;
944 
945  uint32 need_space;
946 
947  if (pSrcItem && pSrcItem->IsNotEmptyBag() && !IsBagPos(uint16(bag) << 8 | slot))
948  return EQUIP_ERR_CAN_ONLY_DO_WITH_EMPTY_BAGS;
949 
950  // empty specific slot - check item fit to slot
951  if (!pItem2 || swap)
952  {
953  if (bag == INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0)
954  {
955  // keyring case
956  if (slot >= KEYRING_SLOT_START && slot < KEYRING_SLOT_START + GetMaxKeyringSize() && !(pProto->BagFamily & BAG_FAMILY_MASK_KEYS))
957  return EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_DOESNT_GO_INTO_BAG;
958 
959  // currencytoken case
960  if (slot >= CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_START && slot < CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_END && !(pProto->IsCurrencyToken()))
961  return EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_DOESNT_GO_INTO_BAG;
962 
963  // prevent cheating
964  if ((slot >= BUYBACK_SLOT_START && slot < BUYBACK_SLOT_END) || slot >= PLAYER_SLOT_END)
965  return EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_DOESNT_GO_INTO_BAG;
966  }
967  else
968  {
969  Bag* pBag = GetBagByPos(bag);
970  if (!pBag)
971  return EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_DOESNT_GO_INTO_BAG;
972 
973  ItemTemplate const* pBagProto = pBag->GetTemplate();
974  if (!pBagProto)
975  return EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_DOESNT_GO_INTO_BAG;
976 
977  if (slot >= pBagProto->ContainerSlots)
978  return EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_DOESNT_GO_INTO_BAG;
979 
980  if (!ItemCanGoIntoBag(pProto, pBagProto))
981  return EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_DOESNT_GO_INTO_BAG;
982  }
983 
984  // non empty stack with space
985  need_space = pProto->GetMaxStackSize();
986  }
987  // non empty slot, check item type
988  else
989  {
990  // can be merged at least partly
991  InventoryResult res = pItem2->CanBeMergedPartlyWith(pProto);
992  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
993  return res;
994 
995  // free stack space or infinity
996  need_space = pProto->GetMaxStackSize() - pItem2->GetCount();
997  }
998 
999  if (need_space > count)
1000  need_space = count;
1001 
1002  ItemPosCount newPosition = ItemPosCount((bag << 8) | slot, need_space);
1003  if (!newPosition.isContainedIn(dest))
1004  {
1005  dest.push_back(newPosition);
1006  count -= need_space;
1007  }
1008  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
1009 }
1010 
1011 InventoryResult Player::CanStoreItem_InBag(uint8 bag, ItemPosCountVec& dest, ItemTemplate const* pProto, uint32& count, bool merge, bool non_specialized, Item* pSrcItem, uint8 skip_bag, uint8 skip_slot) const
1012 {
1013  // skip specific bag already processed in first called CanStoreItem_InBag
1014  if (bag == skip_bag)
1015  return EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_DOESNT_GO_INTO_BAG;
1016 
1017  // skip not existed bag or self targeted bag
1018  Bag* pBag = GetBagByPos(bag);
1019  if (!pBag || pBag == pSrcItem || (pSrcItem && (pSrcItem->GetGUID() == pBag->GetGUID())) )
1020  return EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_DOESNT_GO_INTO_BAG;
1021 
1022  if (pSrcItem && pSrcItem->IsNotEmptyBag())
1023  return EQUIP_ERR_CAN_ONLY_DO_WITH_EMPTY_BAGS;
1024 
1025  ItemTemplate const* pBagProto = pBag->GetTemplate();
1026  if (!pBagProto)
1027  return EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_DOESNT_GO_INTO_BAG;
1028 
1029  // specialized bag mode or non-specilized
1030  if (non_specialized != (pBagProto->Class == ITEM_CLASS_CONTAINER && pBagProto->SubClass == ITEM_SUBCLASS_CONTAINER))
1031  return EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_DOESNT_GO_INTO_BAG;
1032 
1033  if (!ItemCanGoIntoBag(pProto, pBagProto))
1034  return EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_DOESNT_GO_INTO_BAG;
1035 
1036  for (uint32 j = 0; j < pBag->GetBagSize(); j++)
1037  {
1038  // skip specific slot already processed in first called CanStoreItem_InSpecificSlot
1039  if (j == skip_slot)
1040  continue;
1041 
1042  Item* pItem2 = GetItemByPos(bag, j);
1043 
1044  // ignore move item (this slot will be empty at move)
1045  if (pItem2 == pSrcItem)
1046  pItem2 = nullptr;
1047 
1048  // if merge skip empty, if !merge skip non-empty
1049  if ((pItem2 != nullptr) != merge)
1050  continue;
1051 
1052  uint32 need_space = pProto->GetMaxStackSize();
1053 
1054  if (pItem2)
1055  {
1056  // can be merged at least partly
1057  uint8 res = pItem2->CanBeMergedPartlyWith(pProto);
1058  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
1059  continue;
1060 
1061  // descrease at current stacksize
1062  need_space -= pItem2->GetCount();
1063  }
1064 
1065  if (need_space > count)
1066  need_space = count;
1067 
1068  ItemPosCount newPosition = ItemPosCount((bag << 8) | j, need_space);
1069  if (!newPosition.isContainedIn(dest))
1070  {
1071  dest.push_back(newPosition);
1072  count -= need_space;
1073 
1074  if (count == 0)
1075  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
1076  }
1077  }
1078  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
1079 }
1080 
1081 InventoryResult Player::CanStoreItem_InInventorySlots(uint8 slot_begin, uint8 slot_end, ItemPosCountVec& dest, ItemTemplate const* pProto, uint32& count, bool merge, Item* pSrcItem, uint8 skip_bag, uint8 skip_slot) const
1082 {
1083  //this is never called for non-bag slots so we can do this
1084  if (pSrcItem && pSrcItem->IsNotEmptyBag())
1085  return EQUIP_ERR_CAN_ONLY_DO_WITH_EMPTY_BAGS;
1086 
1087  for (uint32 j = slot_begin; j < slot_end; j++)
1088  {
1089  // skip specific slot already processed in first called CanStoreItem_InSpecificSlot
1090  if (INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0 == skip_bag && j == skip_slot)
1091  continue;
1092 
1093  Item* pItem2 = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, j);
1094 
1095  // ignore move item (this slot will be empty at move)
1096  if (pItem2 == pSrcItem)
1097  pItem2 = nullptr;
1098 
1099  // if merge skip empty, if !merge skip non-empty
1100  if ((pItem2 != nullptr) != merge)
1101  continue;
1102 
1103  uint32 need_space = pProto->GetMaxStackSize();
1104 
1105  if (pItem2)
1106  {
1107  // can be merged at least partly
1108  uint8 res = pItem2->CanBeMergedPartlyWith(pProto);
1109  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
1110  continue;
1111 
1112  // descrease at current stacksize
1113  need_space -= pItem2->GetCount();
1114  }
1115 
1116  if (need_space > count)
1117  need_space = count;
1118 
1119  ItemPosCount newPosition = ItemPosCount((INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0 << 8) | j, need_space);
1120  if (!newPosition.isContainedIn(dest))
1121  {
1122  dest.push_back(newPosition);
1123  count -= need_space;
1124 
1125  if (count == 0)
1126  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
1127  }
1128  }
1129  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
1130 }
1131 
1132 InventoryResult Player::CanStoreItem(uint8 bag, uint8 slot, ItemPosCountVec& dest, uint32 entry, uint32 count, Item* pItem, bool swap, uint32* no_space_count) const
1133 {
1134  LOG_DEBUG("entities.player.items", "STORAGE: CanStoreItem bag = %u, slot = %u, item = %u, count = %u", bag, slot, entry, count);
1135 
1136  ItemTemplate const* pProto = sObjectMgr->GetItemTemplate(entry);
1137  if (!pProto)
1138  {
1139  if (no_space_count)
1140  *no_space_count = count;
1141  return swap ? EQUIP_ERR_ITEMS_CANT_BE_SWAPPED : EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_NOT_FOUND;
1142  }
1143 
1144  if (pItem)
1145  {
1146  // you bad chet0rz, wpe pro
1147  if( bag == NULL_BAG && slot == NULL_SLOT )
1148  if( pItem->IsBag() && pItem->IsNotEmptyBag() )
1149  return EQUIP_ERR_CAN_ONLY_DO_WITH_EMPTY_BAGS;
1150 
1151  // Xinef: Removed next bullshit loot generated check
1152  if (pItem->GetGUID() == GetLootGUID())
1153  {
1154  if (no_space_count)
1155  *no_space_count = count;
1156  return EQUIP_ERR_ALREADY_LOOTED;
1157  }
1158 
1159  if (pItem->IsBindedNotWith(this))
1160  {
1161  if (no_space_count)
1162  *no_space_count = count;
1163  return EQUIP_ERR_DONT_OWN_THAT_ITEM;
1164  }
1165  }
1166 
1167  // check count of items (skip for auto move for same player from bank)
1168  uint32 no_similar_count = 0; // can't store this amount similar items
1169  InventoryResult res = CanTakeMoreSimilarItems(entry, count, pItem, &no_similar_count);
1170  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
1171  {
1172  if (count == no_similar_count)
1173  {
1174  if (no_space_count)
1175  *no_space_count = no_similar_count;
1176  return res;
1177  }
1178  count -= no_similar_count;
1179  }
1180 
1181  // in specific slot
1182  if (bag != NULL_BAG && slot != NULL_SLOT)
1183  {
1184  res = CanStoreItem_InSpecificSlot(bag, slot, dest, pProto, count, swap, pItem);
1185  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
1186  {
1187  if (no_space_count)
1188  *no_space_count = count + no_similar_count;
1189  return res;
1190  }
1191 
1192  if (count == 0)
1193  {
1194  if (no_similar_count == 0)
1195  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
1196 
1197  if (no_space_count)
1198  *no_space_count = count + no_similar_count;
1199  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_CARRY_MORE_OF_THIS;
1200  }
1201  }
1202 
1203  // not specific slot or have space for partly store only in specific slot
1204 
1205  // in specific bag
1206  if (bag != NULL_BAG)
1207  {
1208  // search stack in bag for merge to
1209  if (pProto->Stackable != 1)
1210  {
1211  if (bag == INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0) // inventory
1212  {
1213  res = CanStoreItem_InInventorySlots(KEYRING_SLOT_START, CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_END, dest, pProto, count, true, pItem, bag, slot);
1214  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
1215  {
1216  if (no_space_count)
1217  *no_space_count = count + no_similar_count;
1218  return res;
1219  }
1220 
1221  if (count == 0)
1222  {
1223  if (no_similar_count == 0)
1224  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
1225 
1226  if (no_space_count)
1227  *no_space_count = count + no_similar_count;
1228  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_CARRY_MORE_OF_THIS;
1229  }
1230 
1231  res = CanStoreItem_InInventorySlots(INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_START, INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_END, dest, pProto, count, true, pItem, bag, slot);
1232  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
1233  {
1234  if (no_space_count)
1235  *no_space_count = count + no_similar_count;
1236  return res;
1237  }
1238 
1239  if (count == 0)
1240  {
1241  if (no_similar_count == 0)
1242  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
1243 
1244  if (no_space_count)
1245  *no_space_count = count + no_similar_count;
1246  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_CARRY_MORE_OF_THIS;
1247  }
1248  }
1249  else // equipped bag
1250  {
1251  // we need check 2 time (specialized/non_specialized), use NULL_BAG to prevent skipping bag
1252  res = CanStoreItem_InBag(bag, dest, pProto, count, true, false, pItem, NULL_BAG, slot);
1253  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
1254  res = CanStoreItem_InBag(bag, dest, pProto, count, true, true, pItem, NULL_BAG, slot);
1255 
1256  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
1257  {
1258  if (no_space_count)
1259  *no_space_count = count + no_similar_count;
1260  return res;
1261  }
1262 
1263  if (count == 0)
1264  {
1265  if (no_similar_count == 0)
1266  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
1267 
1268  if (no_space_count)
1269  *no_space_count = count + no_similar_count;
1270  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_CARRY_MORE_OF_THIS;
1271  }
1272  }
1273  }
1274 
1275  // search free slot in bag for place to
1276  if (bag == INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0) // inventory
1277  {
1278  // search free slot - keyring case
1279  if (pProto->BagFamily & BAG_FAMILY_MASK_KEYS)
1280  {
1281  uint32 keyringSize = GetMaxKeyringSize();
1282  res = CanStoreItem_InInventorySlots(KEYRING_SLOT_START, KEYRING_SLOT_START + keyringSize, dest, pProto, count, false, pItem, bag, slot);
1283  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
1284  {
1285  if (no_space_count)
1286  *no_space_count = count + no_similar_count;
1287  return res;
1288  }
1289 
1290  if (count == 0)
1291  {
1292  if (no_similar_count == 0)
1293  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
1294 
1295  if (no_space_count)
1296  *no_space_count = count + no_similar_count;
1297  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_CARRY_MORE_OF_THIS;
1298  }
1299 
1300  res = CanStoreItem_InInventorySlots(CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_START, CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_END, dest, pProto, count, false, pItem, bag, slot);
1301  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
1302  {
1303  if (no_space_count)
1304  *no_space_count = count + no_similar_count;
1305  return res;
1306  }
1307 
1308  if (count == 0)
1309  {
1310  if (no_similar_count == 0)
1311  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
1312 
1313  if (no_space_count)
1314  *no_space_count = count + no_similar_count;
1315  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_CARRY_MORE_OF_THIS;
1316  }
1317  }
1318  else if (pProto->IsCurrencyToken())
1319  {
1320  res = CanStoreItem_InInventorySlots(CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_START, CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_END, dest, pProto, count, false, pItem, bag, slot);
1321  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)

1354  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_CARRY_MORE_OF_THIS;
1355  }

1375  if (no_space_count)
1376  *no_space_count = count + no_similar_count;
1377  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_CARRY_MORE_OF_THIS;
1378  }
1379  }
1380  }
1381

1383

1385  if (pProto->Stackable != 1)
1386  {

1439  }

1444  {

1447  continue;

1452  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;

1488  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
1489  {
1490  if (no_space_count)
1491  *no_space_count = count + no_similar_count;
1492  return res;
1493  }
1494 
1495  if (count == 0)
1496  {
1497  if (no_similar_count == 0)
1498  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
1499 
1500  if (no_space_count)

1502  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_CARRY_MORE_OF_THIS;
1503  }
1504  }
1505 
1506  for (uint32 i = INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START; i < INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END; i++)
1507  {

1513  {

1515  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
1516 
1517  if (no_space_count)
1518  *no_space_count = count + no_similar_count;
1519  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_CARRY_MORE_OF_THIS;
1520  }
1521  }
1522  }
1523 
1524  if (pItem && pItem->IsNotEmptyBag())
1525  return EQUIP_ERR_NONEMPTY_BAG_OVER_OTHER_BAG;
1526

1528  res = CanStoreItem_InInventorySlots(INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_START, INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_END, dest, pProto, count, false, pItem, bag, slot);
1529  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
1530  {
1531  if (no_space_count)
1532  *no_space_count = count + no_similar_count;
1533  return res;
1534  }
1535 
1536  if (count == 0)
1537  {
1538  if (no_similar_count == 0)
1539  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
1540 
1541  if (no_space_count)
1542  *no_space_count = count + no_similar_count;
1543  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_CARRY_MORE_OF_THIS;
1544  }
1545 
1546  for (uint8 i = INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START; i < INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END; i++)
1547  {
1548  res = CanStoreItem_InBag(i, dest, pProto, count, false, true, pItem, bag, slot);
1549  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
1550  continue;
1551 
1552  if (count == 0)
1553  {
1554  if (no_similar_count == 0)
1555  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
1556 
1557  if (no_space_count)
1558  *no_space_count = count + no_similar_count;
1559  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_CARRY_MORE_OF_THIS;
1560  }
1561  }
1562 
1563  if (no_space_count)
1564  *no_space_count = count + no_similar_count;
1565 
1566  return EQUIP_ERR_INVENTORY_FULL;
1567 }
1568 
1570 InventoryResult Player::CanStoreItems(Item** pItems, int count) const
1571 {
1572  Item* pItem2;
1573 
1574  // fill space table
1575  int inv_slot_items[INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_END - INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_START];
1576  int inv_bags[INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END - INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START][MAX_BAG_SIZE];
1577  int inv_keys[KEYRING_SLOT_END - KEYRING_SLOT_START];
1578  int inv_tokens[CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_END - CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_START];
1579 
1580  memset(inv_slot_items, 0, sizeof(int) * (INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_END - INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_START));
1581  memset(inv_bags, 0, sizeof(int) * (INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END - INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START) * MAX_BAG_SIZE);
1582  memset(inv_keys, 0, sizeof(int) * (KEYRING_SLOT_END - KEYRING_SLOT_START));
1583  memset(inv_tokens, 0, sizeof(int) * (CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_END - CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_START));
1584 
1585  for (uint8 i = INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_START; i < INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_END; i++)
1586  {
1587  pItem2 = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i);
1588  if (pItem2 && !pItem2->IsInTrade())
1589  inv_slot_items[i - INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_START] = pItem2->GetCount();
1590  }
1591 
1592  for (uint8 i = KEYRING_SLOT_START; i < KEYRING_SLOT_END; i++)
1593  {
1594  pItem2 = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i);
1595  if (pItem2 && !pItem2->IsInTrade())
1596  inv_keys[i - KEYRING_SLOT_START] = pItem2->GetCount();
1597  }
1598 
1599  for (uint8 i = CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_START; i < CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_END; i++)
1600  {
1601  pItem2 = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i);
1602  if (pItem2 && !pItem2->IsInTrade())
1603  inv_tokens[i - CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_START] = pItem2->GetCount();
1604  }
1605 
1606  for (uint8 i = INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START; i < INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END; i++)
1607  if (Bag* pBag = GetBagByPos(i))
1608  for (uint32 j = 0; j < pBag->GetBagSize(); j++)
1609  {
1610  pItem2 = GetItemByPos(i, j);
1611  if (pItem2 && !pItem2->IsInTrade())
1612  inv_bags[i - INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START][j] = pItem2->GetCount();
1613  }
1614 
1615  // check free space for all items
1616  for (int k = 0; k < count; ++k)
1617  {
1618  Item* pItem = pItems[k];
1619 
1620  // no item
1621  if (!pItem)
1622  continue;
1623 
1624  LOG_DEBUG("entities.player.items", "STORAGE: CanStoreItems %i. item = %u, count = %u", k + 1, pItem->GetEntry(), pItem->GetCount());
1625  ItemTemplate const* pProto = pItem->GetTemplate();
1626 
1627  // strange item
1628  if (!pProto)
1629  return EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_NOT_FOUND;
1630 
1631  // Xinef: Removed next bullshit loot generated check
1632  if (pItem->GetGUID() == GetLootGUID())
1633  return EQUIP_ERR_ALREADY_LOOTED;
1634 
1635  // item it 'bind'
1636  if (pItem->IsBindedNotWith(this))
1637  return EQUIP_ERR_DONT_OWN_THAT_ITEM;
1638 
1639  ItemTemplate const* pBagProto;
1640 
1641  // item is 'one item only'
1642  InventoryResult res = CanTakeMoreSimilarItems(pItem);
1643  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
1644  return res;
1645 
1646  // search stack for merge to
1647  if (pProto->Stackable != 1)
1648  {
1649  bool b_found = false;
1650 
1651  for (uint8 t = KEYRING_SLOT_START; t < KEYRING_SLOT_END; ++t)
1652  {
1653  pItem2 = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, t);
1654  if (pItem2 && pItem2->CanBeMergedPartlyWith(pProto) == EQUIP_ERR_OK && inv_keys[t - KEYRING_SLOT_START] + pItem->GetCount() <= pProto->GetMaxStackSize())
1655  {
1656  inv_keys[t - KEYRING_SLOT_START] += pItem->GetCount();
1657  b_found = true;
1658  break;
1659  }
1660  }
1661  if (b_found)
1662  continue;
1663 
1664  for (int t = CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_START; t < CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_END; ++t)
1665  {
1666  pItem2 = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, t);
1667  if (pItem2 && pItem2->CanBeMergedPartlyWith(pProto) == EQUIP_ERR_OK && inv_tokens[t - CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_START] + pItem->GetCount() <= pProto->GetMaxStackSize())
1668  {
1669  inv_tokens[t - CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_START] += pItem->GetCount();
1670  b_found = true;
1671  break;
1672  }
1673  }
1674  if (b_found)
1675  continue;
1676 
1677  for (int t = INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_START; t < INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_END; ++t)
1678  {
1679  pItem2 = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, t);
1680  if (pItem2 && pItem2->CanBeMergedPartlyWith(pProto) == EQUIP_ERR_OK && inv_slot_items[t - INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_START] + pItem->GetCount() <= pProto->GetMaxStackSize())
1681  {
1682  inv_slot_items[t - INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_START] += pItem->GetCount();
1683  b_found = true;
1684  break;
1685  }
1686  }
1687  if (b_found)
1688  continue;
1689 
1690  for (int t = INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START; !b_found && t < INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END; ++t)
1691  {
1692  if (Bag* bag = GetBagByPos(t))
1693  {
1694  if (ItemCanGoIntoBag(pItem->GetTemplate(), bag->GetTemplate()))
1695  {
1696  for (uint32 j = 0; j < bag->GetBagSize(); j++)
1697  {
1698  pItem2 = GetItemByPos(t, j);
1699  if (pItem2 && pItem2->CanBeMergedPartlyWith(pProto) == EQUIP_ERR_OK && inv_bags[t - INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START][j] + pItem->GetCount() <= pProto->GetMaxStackSize())
1700  {
1701  inv_bags[t - INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START][j] += pItem->GetCount();
1702  b_found = true;
1703  break;
1704  }
1705  }
1706  }
1707  }
1708  }
1709  if (b_found)
1710  continue;
1711  }
1712 
1713  // special bag case
1714  if (pProto->BagFamily)
1715  {
1716  bool b_found = false;
1717  if (pProto->BagFamily & BAG_FAMILY_MASK_KEYS)
1718  {
1719  uint32 keyringSize = GetMaxKeyringSize();
1720  for (uint32 t = KEYRING_SLOT_START; t < KEYRING_SLOT_START + keyringSize; ++t)
1721  {
1722  if (inv_keys[t - KEYRING_SLOT_START] == 0)
1723  {
1724  inv_keys[t - KEYRING_SLOT_START] = 1;
1725  b_found = true;
1726  break;
1727  }
1728  }
1729  }
1730 
1731  if (b_found)
1732  continue;
1733 
1734  if (pProto->IsCurrencyToken())
1735  {
1736  for (uint32 t = CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_START; t < CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_END; ++t)
1737  {
1738  if (inv_tokens[t - CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_START] == 0)
1739  {
1740  inv_tokens[t - CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_START] = 1;
1741  b_found = true;
1742  break;
1743  }
1744  }
1745  }
1746 
1747  if (b_found)
1748  continue;
1749 
1750  for (int t = INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START; !b_found && t < INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END; ++t)
1751  {
1752  if (Bag* bag = GetBagByPos(t))
1753  {
1754  pBagProto = bag->GetTemplate();
1755 
1756  // not plain container check
1757  if (pBagProto && (pBagProto->Class != ITEM_CLASS_CONTAINER || pBagProto->SubClass != ITEM_SUBCLASS_CONTAINER) &&
1758  ItemCanGoIntoBag(pProto, pBagProto))
1759  {
1760  for (uint32 j = 0; j < bag->GetBagSize(); j++)
1761  {
1762  if (inv_bags[t - INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START][j] == 0)
1763  {
1764  inv_bags[t - INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START][j] = 1;
1765  b_found = true;
1766  break;
1767  }
1768  }
1769  }
1770  }
1771  }
1772  if (b_found)
1773  continue;
1774  }
1775 
1776  // search free slot
1777  bool b_found = false;
1778  for (int t = INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_START; t < INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_END; ++t)
1779  {
1780  if (inv_slot_items[t - INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_START] == 0)
1781  {
1782  inv_slot_items[t - INVENTORY_SLOT_ITEM_START] = 1;
1783  b_found = true;
1784  break;
1785  }
1786  }
1787  if (b_found)
1788  continue;
1789 
1790  // search free slot in bags
1791  for (int t = INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START; !b_found && t < INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END; ++t)
1792  {
1793  if (Bag* bag = GetBagByPos(t))
1794  {
1795  pBagProto = bag->GetTemplate();
1796 
1797  // special bag already checked
1798  if (pBagProto && (pBagProto->Class != ITEM_CLASS_CONTAINER || pBagProto->SubClass != ITEM_SUBCLASS_CONTAINER))
1799  continue;
1800 
1801  for (uint32 j = 0; j < bag->GetBagSize(); j++)
1802  {
1803  if (inv_bags[t - INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START][j] == 0)
1804  {
1805  inv_bags[t - INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START][j] = 1;
1806  b_found = true;
1807  break;
1808  }
1809  }
1810  }
1811  }
1812 
1813  // no free slot found?
1814  if (!b_found)
1815  return EQUIP_ERR_INVENTORY_FULL;
1816  }
1817 
1818  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
1819 }
1820 
1822 InventoryResult Player::CanEquipNewItem(uint8 slot, uint16& dest, uint32 item, bool swap) const
1823 {
1824  dest = 0;
1825  Item* pItem = Item::CreateItem(item, 1, this);
1826  if (pItem)
1827  {
1828  InventoryResult result = CanEquipItem(slot, dest, pItem, swap);
1829  delete pItem;
1830  return result;
1831  }
1832 
1833  return EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_NOT_FOUND;
1834 }
1835 
1836 InventoryResult Player::CanEquipItem(uint8 slot, uint16& dest, Item* pItem, bool swap, bool not_loading) const
1837 {
1838  dest = 0;
1839  if (pItem)
1840  {
1841  LOG_DEBUG("entities.player.items", "STORAGE: CanEquipItem slot = %u, item = %u, count = %u", slot, pItem->GetEntry(), pItem->GetCount());
1842  ItemTemplate const* pProto = pItem->GetTemplate();
1843  if (pProto)
1844  {
1845  if (!sScriptMgr->CanEquipItem(const_cast<Player*>(this), slot, dest, pItem, swap, not_loading))
1846  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_DO_RIGHT_NOW;
1847 
1848  // item used
1849  if (pItem->m_lootGenerated)
1850  return EQUIP_ERR_ALREADY_LOOTED;
1851 
1852  if (pItem->IsBindedNotWith(this))
1853  return EQUIP_ERR_DONT_OWN_THAT_ITEM;
1854 
1855  // check count of items (skip for auto move for same player from bank)
1856  InventoryResult res = CanTakeMoreSimilarItems(pItem);
1857  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
1858  return res;
1859 
1860  // check this only in game
1861  if (not_loading)
1862  {
1863  // May be here should be more stronger checks; STUNNED checked
1864  // ROOT, CONFUSED, DISTRACTED, FLEEING this needs to be checked.
1865  if (HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_STUNNED))
1866  return EQUIP_ERR_YOU_ARE_STUNNED;
1867 
1868  // do not allow equipping gear except weapons, offhands, projectiles, relics in
1869  // - combat
1870  // - in-progress arenas
1871  if (!pProto->CanChangeEquipStateInCombat())
1872  {
1873  if (IsInCombat())
1874  return EQUIP_ERR_NOT_IN_COMBAT;
1875 
1876  if (Battleground* bg = GetBattleground())
1877  if (bg->isArena() && bg->GetStatus() == STATUS_IN_PROGRESS)
1878  return EQUIP_ERR_NOT_DURING_ARENA_MATCH;
1879  }
1880 
1881  if (IsInCombat() && (pProto->Class == ITEM_CLASS_WEAPON || pProto->InventoryType == INVTYPE_RELIC) && m_weaponChangeTimer != 0)
1882  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_DO_RIGHT_NOW; // maybe exist better err
1883 
1884  if (IsNonMeleeSpellCast(false))
1885  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_DO_RIGHT_NOW;
1886  }
1887 
1888  ScalingStatDistributionEntry const* ssd = pProto->ScalingStatDistribution ? sScalingStatDistributionStore.LookupEntry(pProto->ScalingStatDistribution) : 0;
1889  // check allowed level (extend range to upper values if MaxLevel more or equal max player level, this let GM set high level with 1...max range items)
1890  if (ssd && ssd->MaxLevel < DEFAULT_MAX_LEVEL && ssd->MaxLevel < getLevel())
1891  return EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_CANT_BE_EQUIPPED;
1892 
1893  uint8 eslot = FindEquipSlot(pProto, slot, swap);
1894  if (eslot == NULL_SLOT)
1895  return EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_CANT_BE_EQUIPPED;
1896 
1897  // Xinef: dont allow to equip items on disarmed slot
1898  if (!CanUseAttackType(GetAttackBySlot(eslot)))
1899  return EQUIP_ERR_NOT_WHILE_DISARMED;
1900 
1901  res = CanUseItem(pItem, not_loading);
1902  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
1903  return res;
1904 
1905  if (!swap && GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, eslot))
1906  return EQUIP_ERR_NO_EQUIPMENT_SLOT_AVAILABLE;
1907 
1908  // if we are swapping 2 equiped items, CanEquipUniqueItem check
1909  // should ignore the item we are trying to swap, and not the
1910  // destination item. CanEquipUniqueItem should ignore destination
1911  // item only when we are swapping weapon from bag
1912  uint8 ignore = uint8(NULL_SLOT);
1913  switch (eslot)
1914  {
1915  case EQUIPMENT_SLOT_MAINHAND:
1916  ignore = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_OFFHAND;
1917  break;
1918  case EQUIPMENT_SLOT_OFFHAND:
1919  ignore = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_MAINHAND;
1920  break;
1921  case EQUIPMENT_SLOT_FINGER1:
1922  ignore = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_FINGER2;
1923  break;
1924  case EQUIPMENT_SLOT_FINGER2:
1925  ignore = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_FINGER1;
1926  break;
1927  case EQUIPMENT_SLOT_TRINKET1:
1928  ignore = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_TRINKET2;
1929  break;
1930  case EQUIPMENT_SLOT_TRINKET2:
1931  ignore = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_TRINKET1;
1932  break;
1933  }
1934 
1935  if (ignore == uint8(NULL_SLOT) || pItem != GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, ignore))
1936  ignore = eslot;
1937 
1938  InventoryResult res2 = CanEquipUniqueItem(pItem, swap ? ignore : uint8(NULL_SLOT));
1939  if (res2 != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
1940  return res2;
1941 
1942  // check unique-equipped special item classes
1943  if (pProto->Class == ITEM_CLASS_QUIVER)
1944  for (uint8 i = INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_START; i < INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_END; ++i)
1945  if (Item* pBag = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, i))
1946  if (pBag != pItem)
1947  if (ItemTemplate const* pBagProto = pBag->GetTemplate())
1948  if (pBagProto->Class == pProto->Class && (!swap || pBag->GetSlot() != eslot))
1949  return (pBagProto->SubClass == ITEM_SUBCLASS_AMMO_POUCH)
1950  ? EQUIP_ERR_CAN_EQUIP_ONLY1_AMMOPOUCH
1951  : EQUIP_ERR_CAN_EQUIP_ONLY1_QUIVER;
1952 
1953  uint32 type = pProto->InventoryType;
1954 
1955  if (eslot == EQUIPMENT_SLOT_OFFHAND)
1956  {
1957  // Do not allow polearm to be equipped in the offhand (rare case for the only 1h polearm 41750)
1958  // xinef: same for fishing poles
1959  if (type == INVTYPE_WEAPON && (pProto->SubClass == ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_POLEARM || pProto->SubClass == ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_FISHING_POLE))
1960  return EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_DOESNT_GO_TO_SLOT;
1961 
1962  else if (type == INVTYPE_WEAPON || type == INVTYPE_WEAPONOFFHAND)
1963  {
1964  if (!CanDualWield())
1965  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_DUAL_WIELD;
1966  }
1967  else if (type == INVTYPE_2HWEAPON)
1968  {
1969  if (!CanDualWield() || !CanTitanGrip())
1970  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_DUAL_WIELD;
1971  }
1972 
1973  if (IsTwoHandUsed())
1974  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_EQUIP_WITH_TWOHANDED;
1975  }
1976 
1977  // equip two-hand weapon case (with possible unequip 2 items)
1978  if (type == INVTYPE_2HWEAPON)
1979  {
1980  if (eslot == EQUIPMENT_SLOT_OFFHAND)
1981  {
1982  if (!CanTitanGrip())
1983  return EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_CANT_BE_EQUIPPED;
1984  }
1985  else if (eslot != EQUIPMENT_SLOT_MAINHAND)
1986  return EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_CANT_BE_EQUIPPED;
1987 
1988  if (!CanTitanGrip())
1989  {
1990  // offhand item must can be stored in inventory for offhand item and it also must be unequipped
1991  Item* offItem = GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, EQUIPMENT_SLOT_OFFHAND);
1992  ItemPosCountVec off_dest;
1993  if (offItem && (!not_loading ||
1994  CanUnequipItem(uint16(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0) << 8 | EQUIPMENT_SLOT_OFFHAND, false) != EQUIP_ERR_OK ||
1995  CanStoreItem(NULL_BAG, NULL_SLOT, off_dest, offItem, false) != EQUIP_ERR_OK))
1996  return swap ? EQUIP_ERR_ITEMS_CANT_BE_SWAPPED : EQUIP_ERR_INVENTORY_FULL;
1997  }
1998  }
1999  dest = ((INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0 << 8) | eslot);
2000  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
2001  }
2002  }
2003 
2004  return !swap ? EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_NOT_FOUND : EQUIP_ERR_ITEMS_CANT_BE_SWAPPED;
2005 }
2006 
2007 InventoryResult Player::CanUnequipItem(uint16 pos, bool swap) const
2008 {
2009  if (!sScriptMgr->CanUnequipItem(const_cast<Player*>(this), pos, swap))
2010  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_DO_RIGHT_NOW;
2011 
2012  // Applied only to equipped items and bank bags
2013  if (!IsEquipmentPos(pos) && !IsBagPos(pos))
2014  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
2015 
2016  Item* pItem = GetItemByPos(pos);
2017 
2018  // Applied only to existed equipped item
2019  if (!pItem)
2020  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
2021 
2022  LOG_DEBUG("entities.player.items", "STORAGE: CanUnequipItem slot = %u, item = %u, count = %u", pos, pItem->GetEntry(), pItem->GetCount());
2023 
2024  ItemTemplate const* pProto = pItem->GetTemplate();
2025  if (!pProto)
2026  return EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_NOT_FOUND;
2027 
2028  // item used
2029  if (pItem->m_lootGenerated)
2030  return EQUIP_ERR_ALREADY_LOOTED;
2031 
2032  // do not allow unequipping gear except weapons, offhands, projectiles, relics in
2033  // - combat
2034  // - in-progress arenas
2035  if (!pProto->CanChangeEquipStateInCombat())
2036  {
2037  if (IsInCombat())
2038  return EQUIP_ERR_NOT_IN_COMBAT;
2039 
2040  if (Battleground* bg = GetBattleground())
2041  if (bg->isArena() && bg->GetStatus() == STATUS_IN_PROGRESS)
2042  return EQUIP_ERR_NOT_DURING_ARENA_MATCH;
2043  }
2044 
2045  // Xinef: dont allow to unequip items on disarmed slot
2046  if (!CanUseAttackType(GetAttackBySlot(pItem->GetSlot())))
2047  return EQUIP_ERR_NOT_WHILE_DISARMED;
2048 
2049  if (!swap && pItem->IsNotEmptyBag())
2050  return EQUIP_ERR_CAN_ONLY_DO_WITH_EMPTY_BAGS;
2051 
2052  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
2053 }

2055 InventoryResult Player::CanBankItem(uint8 bag, uint8 slot, ItemPosCountVec& dest, Item* pItem, bool swap, bool not_loading) const
2056 {
2057  if (!pItem)
2058  return swap ? EQUIP_ERR_ITEMS_CANT_BE_SWAPPED : EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_NOT_FOUND;
2059 
2060  uint32 count = pItem->GetCount();
2061 
2062  LOG_DEBUG("entities.player.items", "STORAGE: CanBankItem bag = %u, slot = %u, item = %u, count = %u", bag, slot, pItem->GetEntry(), pItem->GetCount());
2063  ItemTemplate const* pProto = pItem->GetTemplate();
2064  if (!pProto)
2065  return swap ? EQUIP_ERR_ITEMS_CANT_BE_SWAPPED : EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_NOT_FOUND;
2066 
2067  // Xinef: Removed next bullshit loot generated check
2068  if (pItem->GetGUID() == GetLootGUID())
2069  return EQUIP_ERR_ALREADY_LOOTED;
2070 
2071  if (pItem->IsBindedNotWith(this))
2072  return EQUIP_ERR_DONT_OWN_THAT_ITEM;
2073 
2074  // Currency tokens are not supposed to be swapped out of their hidden bag
2075  uint8 pItemslot = pItem->GetSlot();
2076  if (pItemslot >= CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_START && pItemslot < CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_END)
2077  {
2078  LOG_ERROR("entities.player", "Possible hacking attempt: Player %s [%s] tried to move token [%s, entry: %u] out of the currency bag!",
2079  GetName().c_str(), GetGUID().ToString().c_str(), pItem->GetGUID().ToString().c_str(), pProto->ItemId);
2080  return EQUIP_ERR_ITEMS_CANT_BE_SWAPPED;
2081  }
2082 
2083  // check count of items (skip for auto move for same player from bank)
2084  InventoryResult res = CanTakeMoreSimilarItems(pItem);
2085  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
2086  return res;
2087 
2088  // in specific slot
2089  if (bag != NULL_BAG && slot != NULL_SLOT)
2090  {
2091  if (slot >= BANK_SLOT_BAG_START && slot < BANK_SLOT_BAG_END)
2092  {
2093  if (!pItem->IsBag())
2094  return EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_DOESNT_GO_TO_SLOT;
2095 
2096  if (slot - BANK_SLOT_BAG_START >= GetBankBagSlotCount())
2097  return EQUIP_ERR_MUST_PURCHASE_THAT_BAG_SLOT;
2098 
2099  res = CanUseItem(pItem, not_loading);
2100  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
2101  return res;
2102  }
2103 
2104  res = CanStoreItem_InSpecificSlot(bag, slot, dest, pProto, count, swap, pItem);
2105  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
2106  return res;
2107 
2108  if (count == 0)
2109  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
2110  }
2111 
2112  // not specific slot or have space for partly store only in specific slot
2113 
2114  // in specific bag
2115  if (bag != NULL_BAG)
2116  {
2117  if (pItem->IsNotEmptyBag())
2118  return EQUIP_ERR_NONEMPTY_BAG_OVER_OTHER_BAG;
2119 
2120  // search stack in bag for merge to
2121  if (pProto->Stackable != 1)
2122  {
2123  if (bag == INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0)
2124  {
2125  res = CanStoreItem_InInventorySlots(BANK_SLOT_ITEM_START, BANK_SLOT_ITEM_END, dest, pProto, count, true, pItem, bag, slot);
2126  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
2127  return res;
2128 
2129  if (count == 0)
2130  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
2131  }
2132  else
2133  {
2134  res = CanStoreItem_InBag(bag, dest, pProto, count, true, false, pItem, NULL_BAG, slot);
2135  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
2136  res = CanStoreItem_InBag(bag, dest, pProto, count, true, true, pItem, NULL_BAG, slot);
2137 
2138  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
2139  return res;
2140 
2141  if (count == 0)
2142  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
2143  }
2144  }
2145 
2146  // search free slot in bag
2147  if (bag == INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0)
2148  {
2149  res = CanStoreItem_InInventorySlots(BANK_SLOT_ITEM_START, BANK_SLOT_ITEM_END, dest, pProto, count, false, pItem, bag, slot);
2150  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
2151  return res;
2152 
2153  if (count == 0)
2154  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
2155  }
2156  else
2157  {
2158  res = CanStoreItem_InBag(bag, dest, pProto, count, false, false, pItem, NULL_BAG, slot);
2159  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
2160  res = CanStoreItem_InBag(bag, dest, pProto, count, false, true, pItem, NULL_BAG, slot);
2161 
2162  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
2163  return res;
2164 
2165  if (count == 0)
2166  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
2167  }
2168  }
2169 
2170  // not specific bag or have space for partly store only in specific bag
2171 
2172  // search stack for merge to
2173  if (pProto->Stackable != 1)
2174  {
2175  // in slots
2176  res = CanStoreItem_InInventorySlots(BANK_SLOT_ITEM_START, BANK_SLOT_ITEM_END, dest, pProto, count, true, pItem, bag, slot);
2177  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
2178  return res;
2179 
2180  if (count == 0)
2181  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
2182 
2183  // in special bags
2184  if (pProto->BagFamily)
2185  {
2186  for (uint8 i = BANK_SLOT_BAG_START; i < BANK_SLOT_BAG_END; i++)
2187  {
2188  res = CanStoreItem_InBag(i, dest, pProto, count, true, false, pItem, bag, slot);
2189  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
2190  continue;
2191 
2192  if (count == 0)
2193  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
2194  }
2195  }
2196 
2197  for (uint8 i = BANK_SLOT_BAG_START; i < BANK_SLOT_BAG_END; i++)
2198  {
2199  res = CanStoreItem_InBag(i, dest, pProto, count, true, true, pItem, bag, slot);
2200  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
2201  continue;
2202 
2203  if (count == 0)
2204  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
2205  }
2206  }
2207 
2208  // search free place in special bag
2209  if (pProto->BagFamily)
2210  {
2211  for (uint8 i = BANK_SLOT_BAG_START; i < BANK_SLOT_BAG_END; i++)
2212  {
2213  res = CanStoreItem_InBag(i, dest, pProto, count, false, false, pItem, bag, slot);
2214  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
2215  continue;
2216 
2217  if (count == 0)
2218  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
2219  }
2220  }
2221 
2222  // search free space
2223  res = CanStoreItem_InInventorySlots(BANK_SLOT_ITEM_START, BANK_SLOT_ITEM_END, dest, pProto, count, false, pItem, bag, slot);
2224  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
2225  return res;
2226 
2227  if (count == 0)
2228  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
2229 
2230  for (uint8 i = BANK_SLOT_BAG_START; i < BANK_SLOT_BAG_END; i++)
2231  {
2232  res = CanStoreItem_InBag(i, dest, pProto, count, false, true, pItem, bag, slot);
2233  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
2234  continue;
2235 
2236  if (count == 0)
2237  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
2238  }
2239  return EQUIP_ERR_BANK_FULL;
2240 }
2241 
2242 InventoryResult Player::CanUseItem(Item* pItem, bool not_loading) const
2243 {
2244  if (pItem)
2245  {
2246  LOG_DEBUG("entities.player.items", "STORAGE: CanUseItem item = %u", pItem->GetEntry());
2247 
2248  if (!IsAlive() && not_loading)
2249  return EQUIP_ERR_YOU_ARE_DEAD;
2250 
2251  //if (isStunned())
2252  // return EQUIP_ERR_YOU_ARE_STUNNED;
2253 
2254  ItemTemplate const* pProto = pItem->GetTemplate();
2255  if (pProto)
2256  {
2257  if (pItem->IsBindedNotWith(this))
2258  return EQUIP_ERR_DONT_OWN_THAT_ITEM;
2259 
2260  InventoryResult res = CanUseItem(pProto);
2261  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
2262  return res;
2263 
2264  if (pItem->GetSkill() != 0)
2265  {
2266  bool allowEquip = false;
2267  uint32 itemSkill = pItem->GetSkill();
2268  // Armor that is binded to account can "morph" from plate to mail, etc. if skill is not learned yet.
2269  if (pProto->Quality == ITEM_QUALITY_HEIRLOOM && pProto->Class == ITEM_CLASS_ARMOR && !HasSkill(itemSkill))
2270  {
2271  // TODO: when you right-click already equipped item it throws EQUIP_ERR_NO_REQUIRED_PROFICIENCY.
2272 
2273  // In fact it's a visual bug, everything works properly... I need sniffs of operations with
2274  // binded to account items from off server.
2275 
2276  switch (getClass())
2277  {
2278  case CLASS_HUNTER:
2279  case CLASS_SHAMAN:
2280  allowEquip = (itemSkill == SKILL_MAIL);
2281  break;
2282  case CLASS_PALADIN:
2283  case CLASS_WARRIOR:
2284  allowEquip = (itemSkill == SKILL_PLATE_MAIL);
2285  break;
2286  }
2287  }
2288  if (!allowEquip && GetSkillValue(itemSkill) == 0)
2289  return EQUIP_ERR_NO_REQUIRED_PROFICIENCY;
2290  }
2291 
2292  if (pProto->RequiredReputationFaction && uint32(GetReputationRank(pProto->RequiredReputationFaction)) < pProto->RequiredReputationRank)
2293  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_EQUIP_REPUTATION;
2294 
2295  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
2296  }
2297  }
2298  return EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_NOT_FOUND;
2299 }
2300 
2301 InventoryResult Player::CanUseItem(ItemTemplate const* proto) const
2302 {
2303  // Used by group, function NeedBeforeGreed, to know if a prototype can be used by a player
2304 
2305  if (!proto)
2306  {
2307  return EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_NOT_FOUND;
2308  }
2309 
2310  if ((proto->Flags2 & ITEM_FLAGS_EXTRA_HORDE_ONLY) && GetTeamId(true) != TEAM_HORDE)
2311  {
2312  return EQUIP_ERR_YOU_CAN_NEVER_USE_THAT_ITEM;
2313  }
2314 
2315  if ((proto->Flags2 & ITEM_FLAGS_EXTRA_ALLIANCE_ONLY) && GetTeamId(true) != TEAM_ALLIANCE)
2316  {
2317  return EQUIP_ERR_YOU_CAN_NEVER_USE_THAT_ITEM;
2318  }
2319 
2320  if ((proto->AllowableClass & getClassMask()) == 0 || (proto->AllowableRace & getRaceMask()) == 0)
2321  {
2322  return EQUIP_ERR_YOU_CAN_NEVER_USE_THAT_ITEM;
2323  }
2324 
2325  if (proto->RequiredSkill != 0)
2326  {
2327  if (GetSkillValue(proto->RequiredSkill) == 0)
2328  {
2329  return EQUIP_ERR_NO_REQUIRED_PROFICIENCY;
2330  }
2331  else if (GetSkillValue(proto->RequiredSkill) < proto->RequiredSkillRank)
2332  {
2333  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_EQUIP_SKILL;
2334  }
2335  }
2336 
2337  if (proto->RequiredSpell != 0 && !HasSpell(proto->RequiredSpell))
2338  {
2339  return EQUIP_ERR_NO_REQUIRED_PROFICIENCY;
2340  }
2341 
2342  InventoryResult result = EQUIP_ERR_OK;
2343 
2344  if (!sScriptMgr->CanUseItem(const_cast<Player*>(this), proto, result))
2345  {
2346  return result;
2347  }
2348 
2349  if (getLevel() < proto->RequiredLevel)
2350  {
2351  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_EQUIP_LEVEL_I;
2352  }
2353 
2354  // If World Event is not active, prevent using event dependant items
2355  if (proto->HolidayId && !IsHolidayActive((HolidayIds)proto->HolidayId))
2356  {
2357  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_DO_RIGHT_NOW;
2358  }
2359 
2360 #ifdef ELUNA
2361  InventoryResult eres = sEluna->OnCanUseItem(this, proto->ItemId);
2362  if (eres != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
2363  {
2364  return eres;
2365  }
2366 #endif
2367 
2368  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
2369 }
2370 
2371 InventoryResult Player::CanRollForItemInLFG(ItemTemplate const* proto, WorldObject const* lootedObject) const
2372 {
2373  if (!GetGroup() || !GetGroup()->isLFGGroup(true))
2374  return EQUIP_ERR_OK; // not in LFG group
2375 
2376  // check if looted object is inside the lfg dungeon
2377  Map const* map = lootedObject->GetMap();
2378  if (!sLFGMgr->inLfgDungeonMap(GetGroup()->GetGUID(), map->GetId(), map->GetDifficulty()))
2379  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
2380 
2381  if (!proto)
2382  return EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_NOT_FOUND;
2383  // Used by group, function NeedBeforeGreed, to know if a prototype can be used by a player
2384 
2385  const static uint32 item_weapon_skills[MAX_ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON] =
2386  {
2387  SKILL_AXES, SKILL_2H_AXES, SKILL_BOWS, SKILL_GUNS, SKILL_MACES,
2388  SKILL_2H_MACES, SKILL_POLEARMS, SKILL_SWORDS, SKILL_2H_SWORDS, 0,
2389  SKILL_STAVES, 0, 0, SKILL_FIST_WEAPONS,0,
2390  SKILL_DAGGERS, SKILL_THROWN, SKILL_ASSASSINATION, SKILL_CROSSBOWS, SKILL_WANDS,
2391  SKILL_FISHING
2392  }; //Copy from function Item::GetSkill()
2393 
2394  if ((proto->AllowableClass & getClassMask()) == 0 || (proto->AllowableRace & getRaceMask()) == 0)
2395  return EQUIP_ERR_YOU_CAN_NEVER_USE_THAT_ITEM;
2396 
2397  if (proto->RequiredSpell != 0 && !HasSpell(proto->RequiredSpell))
2398  return EQUIP_ERR_NO_REQUIRED_PROFICIENCY;
2399 
2400  if (proto->RequiredSkill != 0)
2401  {
2402  if (!GetSkillValue(proto->RequiredSkill))
2403  return EQUIP_ERR_NO_REQUIRED_PROFICIENCY;
2404  else if (GetSkillValue(proto->RequiredSkill) < proto->RequiredSkillRank)
2405  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_EQUIP_SKILL;
2406  }
2407 
2408  uint8 _class = getClass();
2409 
2410  if (proto->Class == ITEM_CLASS_WEAPON && GetSkillValue(item_weapon_skills[proto->SubClass]) == 0)
2411  return EQUIP_ERR_NO_REQUIRED_PROFICIENCY;
2412 
2413  if (proto->Class == ITEM_CLASS_ARMOR)
2414  {
2415  // Check for shields
2416  if (proto->SubClass == ITEM_SUBCLASS_ARMOR_SHIELD && !(_class == CLASS_PALADIN || _class == CLASS_WARRIOR || _class == CLASS_SHAMAN))
2417  {
2418  return EQUIP_ERR_NO_REQUIRED_PROFICIENCY;
2419  }
2420 
2421  // Check for librams.
2422  if (proto->SubClass == ITEM_SUBCLASS_ARMOR_LIBRAM && _class != CLASS_PALADIN)
2423  {
2424  return EQUIP_ERR_YOU_CAN_NEVER_USE_THAT_ITEM;
2425  }
2426 
2427  // CHeck for idols.
2428  if (proto->SubClass == ITEM_SUBCLASS_ARMOR_IDOL && _class != CLASS_DRUID)
2429  {
2430  return EQUIP_ERR_YOU_CAN_NEVER_USE_THAT_ITEM;
2431  }
2432 
2433  // Check for totems.
2434  if (proto->SubClass == ITEM_SUBCLASS_ARMOR_TOTEM && _class != CLASS_SHAMAN)
2435  {
2436  return EQUIP_ERR_YOU_CAN_NEVER_USE_THAT_ITEM;
2437  }
2438 
2439  // Check for sigils.
2440  if (proto->SubClass == ITEM_SUBCLASS_ARMOR_SIGIL && _class != CLASS_DEATH_KNIGHT)
2441  {
2442  return EQUIP_ERR_YOU_CAN_NEVER_USE_THAT_ITEM;
2443  }
2444  }
2445 
2446  if (proto->Class == ITEM_CLASS_ARMOR && proto->SubClass > ITEM_SUBCLASS_ARMOR_MISC && proto->SubClass < ITEM_SUBCLASS_ARMOR_BUCKLER &&
2447  proto->InventoryType != INVTYPE_CLOAK)
2448  {
2449  uint32 subclassToCompare = ITEM_SUBCLASS_ARMOR_CLOTH;
2450  switch (_class)
2451  {
2452  case CLASS_WARRIOR:
2453  if (proto->HasStat(ITEM_MOD_SPELL_POWER) || proto->HasSpellPowerStat())
2454  {
2455  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_DO_RIGHT_NOW;
2456  }
2457  [[fallthrough]];
2458  case CLASS_DEATH_KNIGHT:
2459  case CLASS_PALADIN:
2460  subclassToCompare = ITEM_SUBCLASS_ARMOR_PLATE;
2461  break;
2462  case CLASS_HUNTER:
2463  case CLASS_SHAMAN:
2464  subclassToCompare = ITEM_SUBCLASS_ARMOR_MAIL;
2465  break;
2466  case CLASS_ROGUE:
2467  if (proto->HasStat(ITEM_MOD_SPELL_POWER) || proto->HasSpellPowerStat())
2468  {
2469  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_DO_RIGHT_NOW;
2470  }
2471  [[fallthrough]];
2472  case CLASS_DRUID:
2473  subclassToCompare = ITEM_SUBCLASS_ARMOR_LEATHER;
2474  break;
2475  default:
2476  break;
2477  }
2478 
2479  if (proto->SubClass > subclassToCompare)
2480  {
2481  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_DO_RIGHT_NOW;
2482  }
2483  else if (sWorld->getIntConfig(CONFIG_LOOT_NEED_BEFORE_GREED_ILVL_RESTRICTION) && proto->ItemLevel > sWorld->getIntConfig(CONFIG_LOOT_NEED_BEFORE_GREED_ILVL_RESTRICTION))
2484  {
2485  if (proto->SubClass < subclassToCompare)
2486  {
2487  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_DO_RIGHT_NOW;
2488  }
2489  }
2490  }
2491 
2492  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
2493 }

2495 InventoryResult Player::CanUseAmmo(uint32 item) const
2496 {
2497  LOG_DEBUG("entities.player.items", "STORAGE: CanUseAmmo item = %u", item);
2498  if (!IsAlive())
2499  return EQUIP_ERR_YOU_ARE_DEAD;
2500  //if (isStunned())
2501  // return EQUIP_ERR_YOU_ARE_STUNNED;
2502  ItemTemplate const* pProto = sObjectMgr->GetItemTemplate(item);
2503  if (pProto)
2504  {
2505  if (pProto->InventoryType != INVTYPE_AMMO)
2506  return EQUIP_ERR_ONLY_AMMO_CAN_GO_HERE;
2507

2509  if (res != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
2510  return res;
2511 
2512  /*if (GetReputationMgr().GetReputation() < pProto->RequiredReputation)
2513  return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_EQUIP_REPUTATION;
2514  */
2515 
2516  // Requires No Ammo
2517  if (HasAura(46699))
2518  return EQUIP_ERR_BAG_FULL6;
2519 
2520  return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
2521  }
2522  return EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_NOT_FOUND;
2523 }

2525 void Player::SetAmmo(uint32 item)
2526 {

2528  return;
2529

2532  return;

2539  return;
2540  }

2543

2563 // Return stored item (if stored to stack, it can diff. from pItem). And pItem ca be deleted in this case.
2564 Item* Player::StoreNewItem(ItemPosCountVec const& dest, uint32 item, bool update, int32 randomPropertyId, AllowedLooterSet& allowedLooters)
2565 {
2566  uint32 count = 0;
2567  for (ItemPosCountVec::const_iterator itr = dest.begin(); itr != dest.end(); ++itr)
2568  count += itr->count;
2569 
2570  Item* pItem = Item::CreateItem(item, count, this, false, randomPropertyId);
2571  if (pItem)
2572  {
2573  // pussywizard: obtaining blue or better items saves to db
2574  if (ItemTemplate const* pProto = sObjectMgr->GetItemTemplate(item))
2575  if (pProto->Quality >= ITEM_QUALITY_RARE)
2576  AdditionalSavingAddMask(ADDITIONAL_SAVING_INVENTORY_AND_GOLD);
2577 
2578  ItemAddedQuestCheck(item, count);
2579  UpdateAchievementCriteria(ACHIEVEMENT_CRITERIA_TYPE_RECEIVE_EPIC_ITEM, item, count);
2580  UpdateAchievementCriteria(ACHIEVEMENT_CRITERIA_TYPE_OWN_ITEM, item, count);
2581  pItem = StoreItem(dest, pItem, update);
2582 
2583  if (allowedLooters.size() > 1 && pItem->GetTemplate()->GetMaxStackSize() == 1 && pItem->IsSoulBound() && sWorld->getBoolConfig(CONFIG_SET_BOP_ITEM_TRADEABLE))
2584  {
2585  pItem->SetSoulboundTradeable(allowedLooters);
2586  pItem->SetUInt32Value(ITEM_FIELD_CREATE_PLAYED_TIME, GetTotalPlayedTime());
2587  AddTradeableItem(pItem);
2588 
2589  // save data
2590  std::ostringstream ss;
2591  AllowedLooterSet::const_iterator itr = allowedLooters.begin();
2592  ss << (*itr).GetCounter();
2593  for (++itr; itr != allowedLooters.end(); ++itr)
2594  ss << ' ' << (*itr).GetCounter();
2595 
2596  CharacterDatabasePreparedStatement* stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_INS_ITEM_BOP_TRADE);
2597  stmt->setUInt32(0, pItem->GetGUID().GetCounter());
2598  stmt->setString(1, ss.str());
2599  CharacterDatabase.Execute(stmt);
2600  }
2601  }
2602  return pItem;
2603 }
2604 
2605 Item* Player::StoreItem(ItemPosCountVec const& dest, Item* pItem, bool update)
2606 {
2607  if (!pItem)
2608  return nullptr;
2609 
2610  Item* lastItem = pItem;
2611  const ItemTemplate* proto = pItem->GetTemplate();
2612 
2613  for (ItemPosCountVec::const_iterator itr = dest.begin(); itr != dest.end();)
2614  {
2615  uint16 pos = itr->pos;
2616  uint32 count = itr->count;
2617 
2618  ++itr;
2619 
2620  if (itr == dest.end())
2621  {
2622  lastItem = _StoreItem(pos, pItem, count, false, update);
2623  break;
2624  }
2625 
2626  lastItem = _StoreItem(pos, pItem, count, true, update);
2627  }
2628 
2629  // cast after item storing - some checks in checkcast requires item to be present!!
2630  if (lastItem)
2631  for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_ITEM_PROTO_SPELLS; ++i)
2632  if (proto->Spells[i].SpellTrigger == ITEM_SPELLTRIGGER_ON_NO_DELAY_USE && proto->Spells[i].SpellId > 0) // On obtain trigger
2633  if (!HasAura(proto->Spells[i].SpellId))
2634  CastSpell(this, proto->Spells[i].SpellId, true, lastItem);
2635 
2636  return lastItem;
2637 }
2638 
2639 // Return stored item (if stored to stack, it can diff. from pItem). And pItem ca be deleted in this case.
2640 Item* Player::_StoreItem(uint16 pos, Item* pItem, uint32 count, bool clone, bool update)
2641 {
2642  if (!pItem)
2643  return nullptr;
2644 
2645  uint8 bag = pos >> 8;
2646  uint8 slot = pos & 255;
2647 
2648  LOG_DEBUG("entities.player.items", "STORAGE: StoreItem bag = %u, slot = %u, item = %u, count = %u, %s", bag, slot, pItem->GetEntry(), count, pItem->GetGUID().ToString().c_str());
2649 
2650  Item* pItem2 = GetItemByPos(bag, slot);
2651 
2652  if (!pItem2)
2653  {
2654  if (clone)
2655  pItem = pItem->CloneItem(count, this);
2656  else
2657  pItem->SetCount(count);
2658 
2659  if (!pItem)
2660  return nullptr;
2661 
2662  if (pItem->GetTemplate()->Bonding == BIND_WHEN_PICKED_UP ||
2663  pItem->GetTemplate()->Bonding == BIND_QUEST_ITEM ||
2664  (pItem->GetTemplate()->Bonding == BIND_WHEN_EQUIPED && IsBagPos(pos)))
2665  pItem->SetBinding(true);
2666 
2667  Bag* pBag = (bag == INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0) ? nullptr : GetBagByPos(bag);
2668  if (!pBag)
2669  {
2670  m_items[slot] = pItem;
2671  SetGuidValue(PLAYER_FIELD_INV_SLOT_HEAD + (slot * 2), pItem->GetGUID());
2672  pItem->SetGuidValue(ITEM_FIELD_CONTAINED, GetGUID());
2673  pItem->SetGuidValue(ITEM_FIELD_OWNER, GetGUID());
2674 
2675  pItem->SetSlot(slot);
2676  pItem->SetContainer(nullptr);
2677 
2678  // need update known currency
2679  if (slot >= CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_START && slot < CURRENCYTOKEN_SLOT_END)
2680  AddKnownCurrency(pItem->GetEntry());
2681  }
2682  else
2683  pBag->StoreItem(slot, pItem, update);
2684 
2685  if (IsInWorld() && update)
2686  {
2687  pItem->AddToWorld();
2688  pItem->SendUpdateToPlayer(this);
2689  }
2690 
2691  pItem->SetState(ITEM_CHANGED, this);
2692  if (pBag)
2693  pBag->SetState(ITEM_CHANGED, this);
2694 
2695  AddEnchantmentDurations(pItem);
2696  AddItemDurations(pItem);
2697 
2698  return pItem;
2699  }
2700  else
2701  {
2702  if (pItem2->GetTemplate()->Bonding == BIND_WHEN_PICKED_UP ||
2703  pItem2->GetTemplate()->Bonding == BIND_QUEST_ITEM ||
2704  (pItem2->GetTemplate()->Bonding == BIND_WHEN_EQUIPED && IsBagPos(pos)))
2705  pItem2->SetBinding(true);
2706 
2707  pItem2->SetCount(pItem2->GetCount() + count);
2708  if (IsInWorld() && update)
2709  pItem2->SendUpdateToPlayer(this);
2710 
2711  if (!clone)
2712  {
2713  // delete item (it not in any slot currently)
2714  if (IsInWorld() && update)
2715  {
2716  pItem->RemoveFromWorld();
2717  pItem->DestroyForPlayer(this);
2718  }
2719 
2720  RemoveEnchantmentDurations(pItem);
2721  RemoveItemDurations(pItem);
2722 
2723  pItem->SetOwnerGUID(GetGUID()); // prevent error at next SetState in case trade/mail/buy from vendor
2724  pItem->SetNotRefundable(this);
2725  pItem->ClearSoulboundTradeable(this);
2726  RemoveTradeableItem(pItem);
2727  pItem->SetState(ITEM_REMOVED, this);
2728  }
2729 
2730  AddEnchantmentDurations(pItem2);
2731 
2732  pItem2->SetState(ITEM_CHANGED, this);
2733 
2734  return pItem2;
2735  }
2736 }

2738 Item* Player::EquipNewItem(uint16 pos, uint32 item, bool update)
2739 {
2740  Item* _item = Item::CreateItem(item, 1, this);
2741  if (!_item)
2742  return nullptr;
2743 
2744  if (!IsEquipmentPos(pos) || sScriptMgr->CanSaveEquipNewItem(this, _item, pos, update))
2745  {
2746  // pussywizard: obtaining blue or better items saves to db
2747  if (ItemTemplate const* pProto = sObjectMgr->GetItemTemplate(item))
2748  if (pProto->Quality >= ITEM_QUALITY_RARE)
2749  AdditionalSavingAddMask(ADDITIONAL_SAVING_INVENTORY_AND_GOLD);
2750 
2751  ItemAddedQuestCheck(item, 1);
2752  UpdateAchievementCriteria(ACHIEVEMENT_CRITERIA_TYPE_RECEIVE_EPIC_ITEM, item, 1);
2753  }
2754 
2755  return EquipItem(pos, _item, update);
2756 }
